 # RupayKG Enterprise
 
+RupayKG is a monorepo with:
+- **FastAPI backend** in `backend/`
+- **Next.js frontend** in `frontend/`
 
-## Environment template
+This project now includes a production-ready Docker Compose setup for **Hostinger VPS** deployments.
 
-Copy the deployment-ready environment template before local runs or when setting platform variables:
+## 1) Environment setup
+
+Copy and edit the environment file before any deployment:
 
 ```bash
 cp .env.example .env
 ```
 
-Update values for your target environment (local, Railway, or Vercel).
+Minimum production values:
+- `ENV=prod`
+- `SYSTEM_STATUS=ACTIVE`
+- `MONGODB_URI=mongodb://mongo:27017` (for Docker Compose internal network)
+- `JWT_SECRET=<strong-random-secret>`
+- `BACKEND_CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-domain.com`
+- `NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLET_BEARER_TOKEN=<optional>`
+
+> For Hostinger setup in this repo, `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` is injected as `/api` in compose so frontend and backend work under one domain.
 
 ---
 
-## Deploying the website to Vercel
+## 2) Deploying to Hostinger VPS (recommended)
 
-This repository includes a Vercel configuration for deploying the Next.js frontend from `frontend/`.
+### Prerequisites on VPS
 
-### 1) Install dependencies locally
+Install Docker + Docker Compose plugin on Ubuntu:
 
 ```bash
-cd frontend
-npm install
+sudo apt-get update
+sudo apt-get install -y ca-certificates curl gnupg
+sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
+curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
+sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg
+
+echo \
+  "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.gpg] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
+  $(. /etc/os-release && echo "$VERSION_CODENAME") stable" | \
+  sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
+
+sudo apt-get update
+sudo apt-get install -y docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin
 ```
 
-### 2) Run a local production build check
+### Deployment steps
 
 ```bash
-npm run build
-```
-
-### 3) Deploy with Vercel CLI
-
-From the repository root:
+git clone <your-repo-url> /opt/rupaykg-enterprise
+cd /opt/rupaykg-enterprise
+cp .env.example .env
+nano .env
 
-```bash
-npx vercel --prod
+./deploy/hostinger-deploy.sh
 ```
 
-When prompted:
-- Set the project root to `./` (the included `vercel.json` handles building `frontend/package.json`).
-- Add `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` to your Vercel environment variables (for example your Railway backend URL).
-- Add `NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLET_BEARER_TOKEN` if your wallet endpoint requires JWT auth.
+This launches:
+- `frontend` on internal port `3000`
+- `backend` on internal port `8080`
+- `mongo` for persistence
+- `nginx` exposing ports `80/443`
 
-### 4) Optional: pull Vercel env vars locally
+### Health check
 
 ```bash
-npx vercel env pull frontend/.env.local
+curl http://<server-ip>/api/health
 ```
 
-Then run:
+Expected response:
 
-```bash
-cd frontend
-npm run dev
+```json
+{"status":"ok"}
 ```
 
